## MCP prompts (underused but useful)

- `detect_impact` — guided pre-commit analysis
- `generate_map` — architecture doc + mermaid from the graph

## Index freshness (graph + embeddings)

- After meaningful code changes: `npm run gitnexus:refresh` (includes `--embeddings`)
- Pre-commit hook runs PDG refresh when hooks installed (`npm run hooks:install`)
- **Missing embeddings** (`stats.embeddings === 0` with symbols indexed) = stale — `agent-refresh` rebuilds vectors
- Embeddings preserved on incremental refresh; `--drop-embeddings` only when rebuilding vectors intentionally
- If MCP says stale after refresh, restart Cursor to reload the MCP server

## MCP unreachable — warn immediately

If GitNexus MCP fails, tell the user: _"GitNexus MCP is unreachable — impact/detect_changes/graph queries unavailable. Falling back to Grep/Read without structural safety checks."_ Do NOT silently fall back. Confirm backend health with `npm run gitnexus:doctor` (probes the GitNexus CLI + registry).

## Kit maintenance commands

| Command | Use |
| --- | --- |
| `npm run gitnexus:agent-refresh` | Rebuild graph + embeddings when stale (autonomous) |
| `npm run gitnexus:doctor` | Probe MCP/CLI backend reachability |
| `npm run gitnexus:agent-review -- <base>` | PR review playbook: detect_changes(compare) + impact per changed symbol |
| `npm run gitnexus:commit-msg` | Draft a graph-grounded commit message (affected flows + modules) from staged changes |
| `npm run gitnexus:map` | Regenerate `docs/ARCHITECTURE.gitnexus.md` from the graph (offline, no API key) |
| `npm run gitnexus:ci` | Merge-time impact gate (blocks high-blast-radius changes with no tests) — see `.github/workflows/gitnexus-ci.yml` |
| `npm run gitnexus:scorecard` | Session enforcement tally (grep→graph, impact/commit gates) |
| `npm run gitnexus:verify` | Full install verification before demoing |

## Workspace contract (non-negotiable)

- `impact` BEFORE editing any function / class / method — report blast radius
- `detect_changes` BEFORE committing
- Warn on HIGH / CRITICAL risk before proceeding
- NEVER find-and-replace renames — use `rename`

